events.description:
*********
RSVP/Register at: https://peatix.com/event/375447
*********

The Mobile Sites (mSite) certification is a professional accreditation that Google offers to individuals, who demonstrate proficiency in basic and advanced aspects of mobile website design and development. A Mobile Sites certification allows individuals to demonstrate that Google recognizes them as an expert in mobile sites.

Agenda:
1-3 pm : Study Jam led by mSite Certified facilitators.
3-5 pm : Attempt the free certification exam.

Important Note:
1. Bring your own laptop
2. You need basic web development skills
3. Study Jam is suitable for programmer with minimum of 3-6 months of experience in building web sites.
3. Study Jam is focus on basic concepts. So may not be suitable for very experienced programmers.

events.name: Android Application Profiling - CodeLab
events.description:
Welcome to this 2:30Hrs instructor lead codelab/hands-on session, you'll learn how to use Android Debugging and Profiling tools, to improve your application performance.

What we'll do
- Intro about Debugging & Profiling Tools (Part of SDK and External)
- Share the Sample Application for Testing
- Hands-On: Session, Network and Energy Profiling

What you'll learn
- How to configure and profile an Android Application
- How to collect, view and analyze the Profiling data.

What you'll need
- Laptop with Latest Android Studio and SDK
- Basic understanding of the Android Application Programming
- An Android Device or Emulator running Android Oreo(8.0) or later

Instructors: Ms Renu and Mr Sachin from Grab.
Join in, get tickets ($5) now on our peatix page: https://peatix.com/event/437114

events.name: Kotlin 101 Workshop by Women Techmakers Singapore
events.description:
Welcome to Women Techmakers (SG) meetup. After a long gap, we are reviving the WTM-SG group activity with this workshop. If learning Kotlin has always been in your wish list, then look no further as this 'Kotlin/Everywhere: Kotlin 101' by Ms. Renu Yadav will help you kickstart your development using Kotlin.

Note: This event is specially for all the amazing women in tech.
( P.S - We don’t mind male participation but we would be glad if you could encourage your female colleagues to attend this event.)

Agenda:

2.15-2:30: Introduction & Getting to know the audience
2:30-2:50: Basics Overview by Ms Renu
2:50-3:50: Quick basic hands-on by Ms Renu
3:50-4:10: Q&A + Closing note by Ms Arwa
4:10-4:20: Promoting WTM and Google IO Extended event
4:20-5:00: Networking

Pre-requisites for the workshop:

* You must have some basic programming skills
* A system meeting requirements for Android Studio as mentioned in
(https://developer.android.com/studio/index.html#Requirements)
* Install latest Android studio following the instructions on
(https://developer.android.com/studio/install)

Key Takeaways:

* Why use Kotlin as a primary android development language
* Interoperability of Kotlin with Java
* Ease of Android development with Kotlin

Looking forward to meet you all at the event :)

events.name: TensorFlow 2.0 Documentation Sprint
events.description:
Agenda:
02:00 PM: Check-in
02:15 PM: Intro to TF 2.0 & Contribute to TF Docs
03:00 PM: Break
03:15 PM: Hands-on [Please bring your own computer]
04:45 PM: Wrap up & Next steps

TensorFlow 2.0 is a major release focused on ease of use and clarity while maintains its flexibility. Would you like to contribute to TF 2.0, learn the PR & review process? You can get started by improving its documentation.

A doc sprint is a way to improve the documentation for an open-source library. We are organizing doc sprint to improve TF documentation.

Come join this docs sprint, where our ML GDEs Jason Zaman and others will walk through how to review and create pull requests for making changes to TF documentation. There will be other TF contributors joining remotely as well.

Target Audience: Ideally you know ML, TF or Python. But it's not a pre-requisite in order to contribute to TF docs. Your interest to learn and contribute is more important.

Resources from GDG Seattle:
Video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wkHkSd6BtJo

events.name: #IamRemarkable workshop by WTM Singapore
events.description:
[Note 1: Women Only Event]
[Note 2: Separate registration for IO Extended]
[Note 3: Registration 08:45AM to 09:00AM ]

Women Techmakers (WTM) Singapore is back again this time with a workshop which we believe will resonate with women from all fields. For the first time ever we organising a "#IamRemarkable" workshop.

But what is #IamRemarkable?

#IamRemarkable is a Google initiative empowering women to improve their self promotion & skills so they can celebrate their achievements in the workplace and beyond

What you will achieve at the end of this workshop?

- You will know the importance of self promotion in your career
- Some simple tools which will help you to practice self promotion

Our Facilitator:
Ms. Arwa Lokhandwala who will help you identify "What makes you remarkable?"

Post that you can directly join us for "Google I/O Extended by GDG SG". You need to register separately for that event.

Link: https://iamremarkable.withgoogle.com/faq

DevFest Singapore 2019 brings together experts across different technologies for sessions and showcases, allowing you to be empowered with new knowledge and skills.
